│ THOUGHT: The miscompilation arises from InstSimplify replacing `select (icmp eq A, B), A, B` with `B`. While this is fine for integers (bitwise equality implies substitutability), it is │
│ incorrect for pointers because even when pointers compare equal (same address), their provenance can differ, and the select should preserve the chosen operand’s provenance. Alive2 shows │
│ the replacement changes provenance by forcing the RHS. To fix, we should avoid this fold for pointer types unless the operands are the same SSA value. I will update InstructionSimplify  │
│ to skip this transform when the type is a pointer.                                                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ grep -Rn "select" llvm/lib/Analysis/InstructionSimplify.cpp && sed -n '1,200p' llvm/lib/Analysis/InstructionSimplify.cpp | sed -n '1,200p' > /tmp/instsimp.cpp && nl -ba                  │
│ llvm/lib/Analysis/InstructionSimplify.cpp | sed -n '1,400p' && sed -i 's/if (match(Cond, m_ICmp(Pred, m_Specific(X), m_Specific(Y))) && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_EQ && X == TrueVal && Y ==  │
│ FalseVal)/if (match(Cond, m_ICmp(Pred, m_Specific(X), m_Specific(Y))) && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_EQ && X == TrueVal && Y == FalseVal && !TrueVal->getType()->isPointerTy())/'               │
│ llvm/lib/Analysis/InstructionSimplify.cpp && submit-patch                                                                                                                                 │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                       │
